{
  "texts": [
    "The results indicate that an α value of 0.3 yields the best performance, demonstrating that appropriate adjustment of α can enhance retrieval effectiveness to a certain extent.",
    "Therefore, we selected α = 0.3 for our retrieval and main experiments.",
    "Additional implementation details are presented in Appendix A.2.",
    "Reranking MethodsAfter the initial retrieval, a reranking phase is employed to enhance the relevance of the retrieved documents, ensuring that the most pertinent information appears at the top of the list.",
    "This phase uses more precise and time-intensive methods to reorder documents effectively, increasing the similarity between the query and the top-ranked documents.We consider two approaches in our reranking module: DLM Reranking, which utilizes classification, and TILDE Reranking, which focuses on query likelihoods."
  ]
}